msgctxt "0000"
msgid "Pretty confident."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: raw
#. 4: pause (long)
#. 5: set_colour (red)
#. 6: reset_colour
#. 7: choice
msgctxt "0"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Yeah? <2.pa>You got the skills to back that\n"
"confidence up?<3.ra>Nothing's more dangerous than a man\n"
"who thinks he can handle the worst, only\n"
"to fall apart when the time comes.\n"
"What do you think?<4.pa> Are you confident\n"
"enough to <5.se_co>prove you got the right stuff<6.re_co>?<7.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: choice
msgctxt "1"
msgid "<1.so>Young man...<2.pa>are you looking to <3.se_co>drill<4.re_co>?<5.ch>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0001"
msgid "Uh, not too confident."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: choice
msgctxt "64"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hm...<2.pa> I don't like the sound of that.\n"
"The monsters out this way are strong\n"
"critters.\n"
"You're sure you don't want to <3.se_co>drill<4.re_co> with\n"
"me some?<5.ch>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0002"
msgid "I'm in a hurry..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (long)
msgctxt "128"
msgid ""
"<1.so>My apologies, then. <2.pa>I didn't mean to\n"
"speak out of turn. <3.pa>Happy trails and\n"
"straight shooting, young man."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0003"
msgid "Sure, I'm game."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0004"
msgid "Prove it how?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0005"
msgid "I've nothing to prove."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0006"
msgid "How do you mean?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0007"
msgid "I do."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0008"
msgid "Go over it again."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0009"
msgid "Sure."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0010"
msgid "Nothing doing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0011"
msgid "I'll register this one."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0012"
msgid "I'll call my own horse."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0013"
msgid "I want to quit."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0014"
msgid "It's nothing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0015"
msgid "Yeah, I quit anyway."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0016"
msgid "Fine, I'll keep going."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0017"
msgid "Not really."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0018"
msgid "That would be nice."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0019"
msgid "I'll buy."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0020"
msgid "I'll sell."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0021"
msgid "I'm fine, thanks."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Accompany_00"
msgid ""
"I'd agree that training with your trusty\n"
"horse is a smart move anytime."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (long)
msgctxt "Accompany_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Head down that path there, and you\n"
"ought to come across a <2.se_co>stable<3.re_co>.<4.pa> Fetch\n"
"your steed from them if you got one."
msgstr ""

#. 1: set_colour (red)
#. 2: reset_colour
msgctxt "Accompany_02"
msgid ""
"Get a horse, mount up, then come talk\n"
"to me <1.se_co>while you're riding high in the\n"
"saddle<2.re_co>."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: choice
msgctxt "AskAgain"
msgid "<1.so>Well? <2.pa>You want to <3.se_co>drill <4.re_co>some more?<5.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: choice
msgctxt "AskAgain_00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>The price hasn't gone down anyâ€”\n"
"<2.se_co>20 rupees<3.re_co>, same as ever. That fine\n"
"with you?<4.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "AskAgain_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Don't be a stranger, young man.<2.pa>\n"
"I'll be waiting here for you, come wind\n"
"or storm."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (long)
#. 5: raw
msgctxt "Explanation_00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Ever heard of <2.se_co>horseback archery<3.re_co>?<4.pa> They\n"
"invented it way out east somewhere.<5.ra>It takes a lot of coordination "
"to shoot\n"
"targets with a bow and arrow from the\n"
"back of a galloping horse.\n"
"I expect you'll run into mounted\n"
"varmints now and again, so this'll be a\n"
"good way to get some practice in."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: set_colour (red)
#. 6: reset_colour
msgctxt "Explanation_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Tell you what...<2.pa> You break <3.se_co>more than 20<4.re_co>\n"
"targets, and I'll hand over my <5.se_co>horse gear<6.re_co>."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: set_colour (red)
#. 6: reset_colour
msgctxt "Explanation_02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Tell you what...<2.pa> You break <3.se_co>more than 23<4.re_co>\n"
"targets, and I'll hand over my <5.se_co>horse gear<6.re_co>."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "GameEnd"
msgid "<1.so>Hold it!<2.pa> Head on back here."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "GameInit_00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>They say youth breeds impulsiveness,\n"
"but it's that kind of quick certainty that'll\n"
"save your hide.<2.pa> Maybe someday soon."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: choice
msgctxt "GameInit_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Now...<2.pa>I'm loath to ask, but would you\n"
"mind forking over <3.se_co>20 rupees <4.re_co>to cover\n"
"some of my costs?<5.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "GameInit_02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Much obliged, young man.<2.pa> I guarantee\n"
"my <3.se_co>drills <4.re_co>are worth twice what you pay."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (long)
msgctxt "GameInit_04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Young man... <2.pa>A straight shooter checks\n"
"his wallet before he antes up, not after.<3.pa>\n"
"Sort yourself out, and come back later."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "GameInit_05"
msgid ""
"<1.so>This here's a service I'm happy to\n"
"provide, but I can't do it for free.<2.pa>\n"
"Don't judge a man for his needs."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "GameInit_06"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Good thinking.<2.pa> Keep it up and you might\n"
"live to be my age."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "GameReady_00"
msgid "<1.so>All right. <2.pa>Then c'mere, young man."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: set_colour (red)
#. 6: reset_colour
msgctxt "GameReady_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You see the <2.se_co>targets <3.re_co>floating out there?<4.pa>\n"
"I'll judge your skill by <5.se_co>how many of 'em\n"
"you pop with your arrows<6.re_co>."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (short)
msgctxt "GameReady_02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Don't you worry about when time's up.<2.pa>\n"
"I'll let you know.<3.pa> Until then, ride hard\n"
"and shoot straight.\n"
"Suppose this goes without saying,\n"
"but you get off your horse, and we're\n"
"done here.\n"
"No way to practice shooting from\n"
"horseback when you're standing around\n"
"on foot, after all."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (long)
msgctxt "GameReady_04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Figure I've said my piece now.<2.pa> Time we\n"
"got started.<3.pa> Best of luck, young man."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "GameReady_05"
msgid "<1.so>I'll explain a bit before we get started."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "GameReady_06"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You need a refresher on how this drill\n"
"works?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "GameReady_07"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Figure it's time we got started. <2.pa>Best of\n"
"luck, young man."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: variable (MiniGame_HorsebackArchery_BreakTargetNum)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: pause (long)
#. 7: raw
#. 8: set_colour (red)
#. 9: reset_colour
msgctxt "GameResult_00_00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hm... You only hit <2.se_co><3.pa><4.va><5.re_co>...<6.pa>\n"
"Nothing to write home about.<7.ra>Might want to shoot from <8.se_co>a "
"trot<9.re_co> some\n"
"more before you jump straight into\n"
"firing at a gallop."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: variable (MiniGame_HorsebackArchery_BreakTargetNum)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: pause (long)
#. 7: pause (short)
#. 8: set_colour (red)
#. 9: reset_colour
#. 10: pause (short)
msgctxt "GameResult_01_00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hm... Well, you hit <2.se_co><3.pa><4.va><5.re_co>...<6.pa>\n"
"Not bad, but I'm not rightly convinced\n"
"you're ready to raise the stakes.\n"
"Hitting your mark at a gallop is no small\n"
"potatoes. <7.pa>Make sure to <8.se_co>keep your eye <9.re_co>on\n"
"the target.\n"
"Here's a reward for seeing it through.<10.pa>\n"
"Keep drilling and you'll get it."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: variable (MiniGame_HorsebackArchery_BreakTargetNum)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: pause (long)
#. 7: raw
#. 8: set_colour (red)
#. 9: reset_colour
#. 10: pause (short)
#. 11: sound
#. 12: pause (long)
msgctxt "GameResult_02_00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hm...<2.se_co><3.pa><4.va> targets<5.re_co>...<6.pa>\n"
"You've got some fire in you, young man.<7.ra>The best archers say "
"<8.se_co>targets seem to\n"
"freeze when they concentrate on them<9.re_co><10.pa>.\n"
"I think you could reach that level too.\n"
"<11.so>Here's a gift to help you on your travels.<12.pa>\n"
"Hope you find a good use for it."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: variable (MiniGame_HorsebackArchery_BreakTargetNum)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: pause (long)
#. 7: pause (short)
#. 8: pause (long)
#. 9: sound
#. 10: pause (long)
msgctxt "GameResult_03_00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hm...<2.se_co><3.pa><4.va> targets<5.re_co>...<6.pa>\n"
"It's been a dog's age since I've seen\n"
"such talent in someone so young.\n"
"What do you mean you're not that\n"
"young? <7.pa>Over 100 years old? <8.pa>Go ahead,\n"
"pull the other one.\n"
"<9.so>Anyway, this gift is my thanks for putting\n"
"on a good show.<10.pa> I'm past needing it,\n"
"and I think you should have it."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "Halt_00"
msgid "<1.so>Hm? <2.pa>What's the matter?<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "Halt_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>That's fair.<2.pa> Course, you won't get your\n"
"money back, if that's what you're after.\n"
"Still planning to quit?<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (long)
msgctxt "Halt_02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Good.<2.pa> No one likes a quitter. <3.pa>There's\n"
"still time, so ride hard and shoot straight."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "Halt_03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I suppose you have your reasons.<2.pa>\n"
"Hope to see you again someday."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: raw
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: choice
msgctxt "Initial"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hello there, young man.<2.pa> I can tell just\n"
"by looking that you're a trained warrior.<3.ra>But tell me this:<4.pa> "
"How confident are you\n"
"in your ability to fight on horseback?<5.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "MyHouse_00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Suit yourself. <2.pa>We'll see how well you and\n"
"your horse act as a team on the field."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Near00"
msgid "Can't miss my drills today."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Near01"
msgid "*snore...*"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Near02"
msgid "Do your worst, rain."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "New"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I'll go fix up the targets. <2.pa>Shouldn't\n"
"be long."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "New_00"
msgid "<1.so>All done now.<2.pa> Let's get drilling again."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (long)
#. 4: set_colour (red)
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "NoHouse"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Now...<2.pa>for a young man interested in\n"
"horseback archery, you seem to be in\n"
"want of a horse. <3.pa>That's no way to <4.se_co>drill<5.re_co>."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Rain"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Training on a rainy day like this can be\n"
"harsh, but it'll do you a world of good\n"
"to tough it out."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "Re_ask"
msgid ""
"<1.so>So I'll ask you again.<2.pa> Don't you want\n"
"a chance to prove you're not all talk?<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Register_00"
msgid "<1.so>Sounds like the right call to me."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: raw
#. 5: set_colour (red)
#. 6: reset_colour
msgctxt "Register_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Head down that path there, and you\n"
"ought to come across a <2.se_co>stable<3.re_co>.<4.ra>They'll "
"<5.se_co>register<6.re_co> your horse for you so\n"
"you can come back and drill here."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: pause (long)
msgctxt "Sleep"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hm?<2.pa> You sure are a night owl,\n"
"aren't you?<3.pa>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: raw
#. 6: choice
msgctxt "Talk00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Can't drill without a <2.se_co>bow and arrows<3.re_co>.<4.pa>\n"
"I'd think that's just common sense.<5.ra>If you need some, I can sell you"
" a few\n"
"of mine. Or I'm open for any sort of\n"
"business! What do you say?<6.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "Talk03"
msgid "<1.so>Anything else you need?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "WhenFallFromHorse_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You and your horse are something else.<2.pa>\n"
"Promise me you won't get careless."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: set_colour (red)
#. 6: reset_colour
#. 7: choice
msgctxt "WildHouse_00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hm...<2.pa> That horse of yours doesn't look\n"
"<3.se_co>registered<4.re_co> to me. Can't have you "
"<5.se_co>drill<6.re_co>\n"
"on an unregistered horse.\n"
"Any ideas?<7.ch>"
msgstr ""

